FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - ARMENIA (SHIRAK): SUSPECTED
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 17 Jul 2006
From: FMD News <fmdnews@ucdavis.edu>
Source: Regnum via Rambler, 17 Jul 2006 [in Russian, translated, edited]
<http://www.rambler.ru/db/news/msg.html?mid=8265740&s=4>

New outbreak in Maliy Marash & Panik
-----------------------------------------------
An outbreak of foot and mouth disease (FMD) has been reported in the
Shiraksyaya region of Armenia. In the village of Maliy Marash, 3
cases of FMD in cattle were reported; in Panik, there were 17 cases
of FMD in cattle. These villages have been quarantined. The State
Veterinary Service reports that the necessary steps for averting the
spread of the disease, in particular vaccinations, [are being
implemented? - Mod.AS].
--
FMD News
FMD Surveillance and Modeling Laboratory
University of California at Davis, USA
<http://fmd.ucdavis.edu/news.php>
<fmdnews@ucdavis.edu>
[Shirak region is in northwest Armenia, bordering Turkey on the west
and Georgia on the north; map at
<http://www.yentravel.am/Assets/maps/map_armenia.jpg>.
The last report from Armenia to the OIE, available on Handistatus II,
dates back to 2002 (disease absent). Confirmation -- or otherwise --
of the current outbreak, and data on the FMD serotype involved, are
anticipated.
FMD is not regarded as a zoonosis; a review, including photographs,
is available at
<http://www.vet.uga.edu/vpp/gray_book/FAD/FMD.htm>.
- Mod.AS]
See Also
